    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>The inclosed will inform you that the box with the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0013">2d part of the Tour</title></bibl>
                    was sent this week to <placeName ref="pl0759">your house in Town</placeName>. <persName ref="pe0014">Moses</persName>
                    will soon form a bill &amp; hopes the whole will meet <choice><abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></abbr><expan>your</expan></choice>
                    approbation. The <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">first part</title></bibl> came safe: &amp; shall be
                    returned at Christmas. a beginning is made to <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0032">the journey to London</title></bibl>. The weather
                        in these parts is dreadful &amp; must add to our calamities. I am</p>
                <closer><salute>Dear Sir
                    <lb/><choice><abbr>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> affect:</abbr><expan>Your affectionate</expan></choice> humble <choice><abbr>Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></abbr><expan>Servant</expan></choice></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232"><choice><abbr>Tho.</abbr><expan>Thomas</expan></choice> Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> <choice><abbr>Aug.</abbr><expan>August</expan></choice> 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1782.</dateline></closer>
                </div>
        </body>
